<X|X>
X=(X_1,\ldots,X_n)^T
n
X-E[X]
E[X]=(E[X_1],\ldots,E[X_n])^T=(\mu_1,\ldots,\mu_n) 
 (X-E[X])^T(X-E[X])= \begin{bmatrix} X_1-\mu_1 &\cdots &X_n-\mu_n \end{bmatrix} \begin{bmatrix} X_1-\mu_1\\ \vdots\\ X_n-\mu_n \end{bmatrix} =\sum_{i=1}^n(X_i-\mu_i)^2 
 E[(X-E[X])^T(X-E[X])]=\sum_{i=1}^n E[(X_i-\mu_i)^2]=\sum_{i=1}^n\mathrm{Var}(X_i). 
